Rahas stood in the makeshift laboratory, looking at the patterns on the oscilloscope screen.
Something&rsquo;s not right&hellip;
Something&rsquo;s still wrong&hellip;
I&rsquo;m still not working properly&hellip;
They looked down at the switchboard on their chest. It was supposed to integrate the signals from the different parts of their mind, but it wasn&rsquo;t. At least, not correctly.
They looked over at the grimy sheet of graph paper, and at the official wiring diagram next to it.
